                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/865</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A joint commission of Senators and Deputies has been appointed to investigate
                    railroad matters. Mr. Norton will present railroad’s case to the commission. He
                    informs me that the new administration seems to be friendly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Belden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
